{
  "step_by_step_reasoning": "We trace the architecture chronologically. 1. Web/mobile clients access the platform through API Gateway, triggering a Lambda that reads/writes to MongoDB (external software). 2. For scheduled match initialization, CloudWatch triggers a second Lambda that moves match data from MongoDB to S3. 3. External Game APIs push real-time score changes to a third Lambda, which updates S3. 4. EMR runs Spark jobs to read data from S3, compute rankings, and update MongoDB for real-time leaderboard access. 5. S3 data is loaded into Redshift for historical analytics and coupon targeting.",
